1. An invoice has an amount and a number of days overdue.
2. A company has a name and a list of invoices.
3. The total revenue is the sum of all invoice amounts.
4. The overdue count is the number of invoices with more than 30 days overdue.
5. The overdue amount is the sum of amounts of invoices with more than 30 days overdue.
6. The risk score is: 2 if all invoices are overdue, 1 if any are overdue, otherwise 0.
